task.summary: Default task
Ugly changes for due-in-two-weeks paper experiments
trying to increase parallelism
exporting graph def
added true random rollout (multiprocessing since we aren't using NN)

added metrics, unfinished policy net class, moved code, cleaned up code for random rollouts and such, more testing, re-added including top n children as tests on incorrectly predicted moves revealed high percent differences between predicted moves and correct moves
rollout from the final move not node passed in, put threshold back as top 6 killed performance
found the bug: batch expansion was only including one node from each depth
added tensorboard stuff to policy net training
added a selection for a random child instead of UCT for "rollouts"
changed backprop numbers and which children to update/keep
changed eval to return a percentage too, moved print statement outside to give search more time
Many things added. Main thing: RL. Warning: The code is so ugly now from doing so many modifications for the paper.
logging and appending new roots for tree and DAgger
merging code from mac branch. changed wanderer to play white
true win/loss field + separate policy nets (white: all moves; black: winning moves)
Different NeuralNet Classes, choosing moves based on net true wins
added new tiers for filtering, filtering based on color, put back batch expansions (EOG after height 40)
added enumeration by piece arrays
changed to play 93M node Wanderer, misc
Cythonized, changed NN index sorting to bottleneck argpartsort, changed gameover value to 2^16
Alphago Win scaling
updated pruning and bottleneck
scaled UCT by AGO scaling
changed reexpansion for player moves at the end of the game instead of the beginning
fixed the reexpansion bugs I think?
fixed last bug?
Added cheat mode (keep searching while opponent is thinking)
added real random rollouts. Still very inefficient.
added ept to the rollouts to make them faster. EOG rollouts after height 40
trying PUCT variant
tuning pruning. Choosing most visited, using PUCT and ground truth to steer tree search.
Added a move prediction LSTM. (more for class project than something useful)
CNN RNN
Fixed CNN conversion to RNN data. better initalization to rnn.
new net and tweaking search parameters
tried to make conversion to NN input more efficient
Since we now keep all children, changed flow so we don't have to sort the entire 155 element transition vector
doing all copies and deepcopies by hand
further optimizing (C-ified UCT calculation)
turned treenode into dict. Some bug somewhere?
made subtree check flag backpropagate, removed best child choice (threads not respecting flags)
penalizing moves from key home row areas (domain knowledge :'( )
fixed penalization (ignore for game-saving moves)
fixed bug when children returned None
1 step lookahead for a loss
redid control flow a bit
since 1 step lookahead gameover exists, prioritize choosing true gameovers vs. a win_status when possible
turned sim info into dict, only penalize if opponent not in home territory
pseudo-pruning now. eval children in batches
